1092
00:49:24,383 --> 00:49:25,470
She started waving it around

1093
00:49:25,470 --> 00:49:29,233
like a martial arts type of
things and she cut herself.

1094
00:49:29,233 --> 00:49:30,467
(children yelling)

1095
00:49:30,467 --> 00:49:33,634
(church bell tolling)

1096
00:49:36,943 --> 00:49:38,720
- I'm sorry.

1097
00:49:38,720 --> 00:49:40,120
- [Mary Beth] I'm sorry too.

1098
00:49:43,235 --> 00:49:45,340
- Can I still go to
Brittany's birthday party?

1099
00:49:45,340 --> 00:49:46,173
- Next year.

1100
00:49:47,455 --> 00:49:50,523
(children yelling)

1101
00:49:50,523 --> 00:49:53,356
(whistle blowing)

1102
00:50:11,437 --> 00:50:13,620
(Matthew sighing)

1103
00:50:13,620 --> 00:50:15,153
- [Matthew] You like what you do?

1104
00:50:17,850 --> 00:50:19,200
- What do I what?

1105
00:50:19,200 --> 00:50:21,660
- I honestly don't know
many police officers.

1106
00:50:21,660 --> 00:50:22,493
Do you like it?

1107
00:50:26,620 --> 00:50:29,533
- Actually, I don't even think
about it that way anymore.

1108
00:50:30,760 --> 00:50:32,003
I do it very well,

1109
00:50:32,920 --> 00:50:34,590
and I've been doing it for so long

1110
00:50:34,590 --> 00:50:37,930
that it stopped being
about, "Well, do I like it."

1111
00:50:37,930 --> 00:50:39,323
It's just what I am.

1112
00:50:40,720 --> 00:50:42,373
There's something to be said for,

1113
00:50:44,530 --> 00:50:46,610
not that it's always comfortable

1114
00:50:46,610 --> 00:50:47,940
because that wouldn't describe it.

1115
00:50:47,940 --> 00:50:52,483
But, when I'm working, it's my world.

1116
00:50:53,890 --> 00:50:55,500
It's home base.

1117
00:50:55,500 --> 00:50:58,940
And I think that means more than just

1118
00:50:58,940 --> 00:51:01,203
do you like it or not.

1119
00:51:01,203 --> 00:51:02,740
- Maybe.

1120
00:51:02,740 --> 00:51:04,660
- Now that's not to say that

1121
00:51:04,660 --> 00:51:06,347
once or twice a year I don't start saying,

1122
00:51:06,347 --> 00:51:08,567
"Oh, I pissed it all away.

1123
00:51:08,567 --> 00:51:11,127
"I'm just a beat cop
who became a lieutenant

1124
00:51:11,127 --> 00:51:12,597
"and stalled right there."

1125
00:51:14,565 --> 00:51:16,680
But that's just the blues.

1126
00:51:16,680 --> 00:51:17,880
What incredible insight.

1127
00:51:22,580 --> 00:51:24,080
I don't even know what you do.

1128
00:51:28,480 --> 00:51:33,350
- Well, I started
importing exotic hardwoods.

1129
00:51:33,350 --> 00:51:36,339
The most beautiful wood in the world.

1130
00:51:36,339 --> 00:51:37,370
- Really?

1131
00:51:37,370 --> 00:51:39,630
- But I don't do that anymore.

1132
00:51:39,630 --> 00:51:40,800
My business grew,

1133
00:51:40,800 --> 00:51:43,850
and I got an offer that was irresistible.

1134
00:51:43,850 --> 00:51:45,840
So I sold my import business

1135
00:51:45,840 --> 00:51:50,240
and I invested in a small
telecommunications company,

1136
00:51:50,240 --> 00:51:52,260
which did very well.

1137
00:51:52,260 --> 00:51:53,390
And the years have passed,

1138
00:51:53,390 --> 00:51:56,853
and now I'm an investor.

1139
00:51:57,930 --> 00:51:58,780
- Do you like it?

1140
00:51:59,660 --> 00:52:00,510
- I'm good at it.

1141
00:52:02,660 --> 00:52:04,273
- You're a very successful man.

1142
00:52:06,430 --> 00:52:07,620
- Yes, I am, aren't I?

1143
00:52:13,780 --> 00:52:15,373
I'm a very successful man.

1144
00:52:29,013 --> 00:52:30,670
- [Harvey] I'm not saying
it's not important, Mary Beth.

1145
00:52:30,670 --> 00:52:31,650
I'm saying there's no reason

1146
00:52:31,650 --> 00:52:34,090
to keep her away from a birthday party.

1147
00:52:34,090 --> 00:52:36,628
- Can't it wait, please,
even for a minute.

1148
00:52:36,628 --> 00:52:38,150
(TV show blaring)

1149
00:52:38,150 --> 00:52:39,680
TV goes off please.

1150
00:52:39,680 --> 00:52:41,290
- This is just what my folks did.

1151
00:52:41,290 --> 00:52:42,390
Kid screws up, and suddenly

1152
00:52:42,390 --> 00:52:44,770
the whole house falls in punishment mode.

1153
00:52:44,770 --> 00:52:46,290
Events get canceled.

1154
00:52:46,290 --> 00:52:47,250
Traffic stops.

1155
00:52:47,250 --> 00:52:49,545
- No, Harv, we're not getting
off into what happened to you.

1156
00:52:49,545 --> 00:52:51,780
- I'm saying that my parents
were wrong, Mary Beth.

1157
00:52:51,780 --> 00:52:53,200
- No, Harvey!

1158
00:52:53,200 --> 00:52:56,280
Ordinary and normal are over
in this house for a minute!

1159
00:52:56,280 --> 00:52:58,660
I want this kid stopped cold by this.

1160
00:52:58,660 --> 00:52:59,720
- Don't you think the cut on the hand

1161
00:52:59,720 --> 00:53:01,800
is a pretty good lesson in
not to play with knives.

1162
00:53:01,800 --> 00:53:03,460
- That's not the lesson
I want her to learn!

1163
00:53:03,460 --> 00:53:04,293
- Oh?

1164
00:53:04,293 --> 00:53:06,450
- I want her to learn that you
can't prove you're a big girl

1165
00:53:06,450 --> 00:53:07,900
by intimidating other children.

1166
00:53:07,900 --> 00:53:09,190
There's an element of bullying in it.

1167
00:53:09,190 --> 00:53:10,250
- Bullying, Alice?
- I'm gonna put

1168
00:53:10,250 --> 00:53:11,160
a stop to it now!

1169
00:53:11,160 --> 00:53:14,200
- Well, I couldn't possibly
disagree with you more.

1170
00:53:14,200 --> 00:53:15,210
- I'm right about this.

1171
00:53:15,210 --> 00:53:17,750
- No way this is just a
case of forbidden fruit.

1172
00:53:17,750 --> 00:53:18,890
She couldn't resist.

1173
00:53:18,890 --> 00:53:20,710
So she's suffering the consequences.

1174
00:53:20,710 --> 00:53:22,240
Nine-years-olds learn
this stuff every day.

1175
00:53:22,240 --> 00:53:23,610
- Well, this nine-year-old

1176
00:53:23,610 --> 00:53:25,310
is gonna miss out on Brittany's birthday,

1177
00:53:25,310 --> 00:53:27,220
and she's gonna lose her
allowance for two weeks.

1178
00:53:27,220 --> 00:53:29,680
And there's no TV for a month!

1179
00:53:29,680 --> 00:53:30,970
- [Harvey] That is nuts!

1180
00:53:30,970 --> 00:53:34,760
- And bedtime is 7:30
until further notice!

1181
00:53:34,760 --> 00:53:36,900
(onions sizzling)

1182
00:53:36,900 --> 00:53:37,890
- God help you, Alice.

1183
00:53:37,890 --> 00:53:40,930
Your mother's learned a
taste for the hard line.!

1184
00:53:40,930 --> 00:53:41,850
- [Mary Beth] What did you say?

1185
00:53:41,850 --> 00:53:43,300
- I say keep your capital punishment

1186
00:53:43,300 --> 00:53:44,600
in the courtroom, Mary Beth.

1187
00:53:44,600 --> 00:53:46,343
Save it for Raymond Bolzer.

1188
00:53:50,241 --> 00:53:52,868
Oh, I'm taking Alice to the
birthday party tomorrow.

1189
00:53:52,868 --> 00:53:55,500
(onions sizzling)

1190
00:53:55,500 --> 00:53:56,333
- Oh, geez!

1191
00:54:01,920 --> 00:54:03,830
- [Christine] I love these pictures

1192
00:54:03,830 --> 00:54:06,260
every single one of them.

1193
00:54:06,260 --> 00:54:09,460
- She never got around to
putting them on the walls.

1194
00:54:09,460 --> 00:54:10,810
- They're Darcy.

1195
00:54:10,810 --> 00:54:11,970
Did she shoot these?

1196
00:54:11,970 --> 00:54:12,953
- She was good.

1197
00:54:13,919 --> 00:54:14,857
- Very.

1198
00:54:14,857 --> 00:54:16,853
Do you know how she managed this one?

1199
00:54:17,800 --> 00:54:19,820
- Everyone looks so
natural, nobody's posed.

1200
00:54:19,820 --> 00:54:20,720
How did she do it?

1201
00:54:20,720 --> 00:54:21,940
- Well, there are cameras

1202
00:54:21,940 --> 00:54:23,830
with the lens at a 90-degree angle,

1203
00:54:23,830 --> 00:54:24,790
so you're pointing this way.

1204
00:54:24,790 --> 00:54:26,930
But you're actually shooting that way.

1205
00:54:26,930 --> 00:54:28,593
- So the subject never knows.

1206
00:54:30,560 --> 00:54:32,560
- She still had a couple
of cameras I gave her.

1207
00:54:32,560 --> 00:54:35,470
And now surprise because Patina and I

1208
00:54:36,680 --> 00:54:39,450
we tried rewarding Darcy
for staying clean and sober.

1209
00:54:39,450 --> 00:54:42,363
So I gave her every camera I had.

1210
00:54:43,240 --> 00:54:45,240
I filled the refrigerator with film

1211
00:54:46,170 --> 00:54:47,870
and we never saw anymore pictures.

1212
00:54:49,135 --> 00:54:51,750
- Well, it sounds like
you were very good to her.

1213
00:54:51,750 --> 00:54:53,750
You paid for this place too, didn't you?

1214
00:54:55,010 --> 00:54:56,450
- Yes, I did.

1215
00:54:56,450 --> 00:54:58,900
However, we warned Darcy

1216
00:54:59,900 --> 00:55:01,930
that if she didn't obey our rules,

1217
00:55:01,930 --> 00:55:02,763
she'd have to make her own way

1218
00:55:02,763 --> 00:55:04,960
in the world without our help.

1219
00:55:04,960 --> 00:55:08,800
So, she takes up with a man

1220
00:55:08,800 --> 00:55:11,017
who makes his living selling drugs.

1221
00:55:11,017 --> 00:55:13,130
(slams candle in box)

1222
00:55:13,130 --> 00:55:14,023
Costa Rican.

1223
00:55:18,570 --> 00:55:21,723
And in the first month, he broke her arm.

1224
00:55:23,750 --> 00:55:25,150
Yeah.

1225
00:55:25,150 --> 00:55:26,933
And I went crazy.

1226
00:55:28,770 --> 00:55:31,310
Sight unseen, I hire a completely

1227
00:55:31,310 --> 00:55:34,303
unscrupulous private
investigator named Yap.

1228
00:55:35,774 --> 00:55:38,710
And we had long phone
conversations Mr. Yap and I

1229
00:55:38,710 --> 00:55:40,510
cooking up every scheme in the book.

1230
00:55:41,440 --> 00:55:44,710
And in a way it was
wonderful talking to a guy

1231
00:55:44,710 --> 00:55:46,960
who would do anything
if the price was right.

1232
00:55:46,960 --> 00:55:48,560
- [Christine] You're right that is crazy.

1233
00:55:48,560 --> 00:55:49,393
- Yeah.

1234
00:55:49,393 --> 00:55:51,440
- You never even met this man?

1235
00:55:51,440 --> 00:55:52,273
- Right.

1236
00:55:53,660 --> 00:55:56,120
So, (sighing)

1237
00:55:56,120 --> 00:55:59,413
We agreed to kidnap Darcy.

1238
00:56:00,520 --> 00:56:02,513
We called it an intervention.

1239
00:56:04,610 --> 00:56:05,953
So he snatches her.

1240
00:56:07,200 --> 00:56:09,250
We put her into Watch Hill for treatment.

1241
00:56:15,458 --> 00:56:18,875
My wife Patina never forgave me for that.

1242
00:56:23,015 --> 00:56:25,515
And what we had just collapsed

1243
00:56:29,300 --> 00:56:31,150
under the weight of Darcy's troubles.

1244
00:56:34,176 --> 00:56:35,789
- Was that the end of Mr. Yap?

1245
00:56:35,789 --> 00:56:38,400
- Oh, no, of course not.

1246
00:56:38,400 --> 00:56:41,263
He called now and then to
offer follow up services.

1247
00:56:42,680 --> 00:56:46,523
He even swore that Darcy was
seeing the drug dealer again.

1248
00:56:48,490 --> 00:56:49,923
Now Darcy swore,

1249
00:56:51,020 --> 00:56:53,610
with every gesture possible,

1250
00:56:53,610 --> 00:56:54,653
that it wasn't true.

1251
00:56:55,657 --> 00:56:58,403
"Please, daddy, believe me.

1252
00:56:59,759 --> 00:57:00,592
(scoffs)

1253
00:57:00,592 --> 00:57:01,457
"Please."

1254
00:57:06,430 --> 00:57:08,930
And I had to chose between the word

1255
00:57:10,260 --> 00:57:15,260
of a gross, greedy, unprincipled stranger,

1256
00:57:18,250 --> 00:57:21,903
and the word of my own daughter.

1257
00:57:24,820 --> 00:57:28,683
And I believed him.

1258
00:57:34,280 --> 00:57:35,770
For the rest of my life

1259
00:57:37,340 --> 00:57:38,990
I'm gonna have to live with that.

1260
00:57:42,280 --> 00:57:43,380
- You'd been burned before.

1261
00:57:43,380 --> 00:57:44,503
It's understandable.

1262
00:57:45,879 --> 00:57:49,093
- You can afford to be generous.

1263
00:57:49,093 --> 00:57:51,003
You didn't make the choice.

1264
00:57:53,900 --> 00:57:54,733
That killed her.

1265
00:57:58,590 --> 00:58:00,790
- Matt, somebody's gotta
cut you some slack,

1266
00:58:01,660 --> 00:58:03,460
and it's obviously not gonna be you.

1267
00:58:04,300 --> 00:58:06,333
So, I vote for me.

1268
00:58:32,361 --> 00:58:34,120
- So you're working Saturdays too, huh?

1269
00:58:34,120 --> 00:58:36,260
- Hey, trying to make
a dent in my messages.

1270
00:58:36,260 --> 00:58:37,350
You?

1271
00:58:37,350 --> 00:58:38,477
- I'm gonna grab a bite to eat.

1272
00:58:38,477 --> 00:58:39,373
You wanna come?

1273
00:58:40,300 --> 00:58:41,400
- Nah, I brought mine.

1274
00:58:42,890 --> 00:58:43,723
- Come on.

1275
00:58:44,580 --> 00:58:45,603
I'll bring you back.

1276
00:58:46,687 --> 00:58:47,520
(bag rattles)

1277
00:58:47,520 --> 00:58:48,970
See, you shouldn't eat alone.

1278
00:58:55,612 --> 00:58:58,640
This is a beautiful little girl.

1279
00:58:58,640 --> 00:59:00,850
And now this beautiful child

1280
00:59:00,850 --> 00:59:02,690
takes a weapon to school.

1281
00:59:02,690 --> 00:59:04,010
Harvey says I'm making too much of it,

1282
00:59:04,010 --> 00:59:06,450
but to me, (sighs)

1283
00:59:06,450 --> 00:59:07,990
it's like we're watching her innocence die

1284
00:59:07,990 --> 00:59:09,370
in front of our eyes.

1285
00:59:09,370 --> 00:59:11,520
- Yeah, well, you see more than him.

1286
00:59:11,520 --> 00:59:12,920
- [Mary Beth] No,
Harvey's very perceptive.

1287
00:59:12,920 --> 00:59:13,753
- No, don't get me wrong.

1288
00:59:13,753 --> 00:59:15,150
I'm saying because you were a cop,

1289
00:59:15,150 --> 00:59:16,450
you've seen more than him.

1290
00:59:17,370 --> 00:59:18,700
You've seen evil.

1291
00:59:18,700 --> 00:59:19,533
You've smelled evil.

1292
00:59:19,533 --> 00:59:20,873
You know evil exists.

1293
00:59:22,040 --> 00:59:24,090
I go through the same thing with Maureen.

1294
00:59:25,593 --> 00:59:27,620
Hell, I go through the same
things with the lawyers.

1295
00:59:27,620 --> 00:59:28,453
- [Mary Beth] Yeah.

1296
00:59:28,453 --> 00:59:30,270
- I don't care how many crime scenes

1297
00:59:30,270 --> 00:59:32,145
a guy like Doug Trayne visits.

1298
00:59:32,145 --> 00:59:33,650
- It's not the same.
- Not the same.

1299
00:59:33,650 --> 00:59:34,483
They don't know.

1300
00:59:36,300 --> 00:59:37,640
No, I don't think you're crazy

1301
00:59:37,640 --> 00:59:40,806
for wanting your kid to
stay descent, Mary Beth.

1302
00:59:40,806 --> 00:59:42,574
I think, it's the world that's crazy.

1303
00:59:42,574 --> 00:59:45,157
(bright music)

1304
00:59:56,097 --> 00:59:58,170
- You know I collected cameras for years.

1305
00:59:58,170 --> 01:00:00,870
My grandfather he was an architect,

1306
01:00:00,870 --> 01:00:02,220
and right after he died,

1307
01:00:02,220 --> 01:00:04,940
I started photographing buildings.

1308
01:00:04,940 --> 01:00:08,420
Of course, I tried to get Darcy
interested in it but no, no.

1309
01:00:08,420 --> 01:00:11,132
She only wanted to take
pictures of people.

1310
01:00:11,132 --> 01:00:13,477
- Well, I'm with her.

1311
01:00:13,477 --> 01:00:16,172
(bright music)

1312
01:00:16,172 --> 01:00:17,763
What do you think of that building?

1313
01:00:19,710 --> 01:00:21,093
- Why you like those buildings?

1314
01:00:23,070 --> 01:00:26,078
- Well, yeah.

1315
01:00:26,078 --> 01:00:27,853
- Well, then get out of the way.

1316
01:00:27,853 --> 01:00:29,853
Sit over there.
- Sorry.

1317
01:00:31,324 --> 01:00:32,491
- There we go.

1318
01:00:35,644 --> 01:00:38,823
(camera beeps and flashes)

1319
01:00:38,823 --> 01:00:41,530
(camera whirring)

1320
01:00:41,530 --> 01:00:42,740
- I'm surprised a gumball

