01:00:44,830 --> 01:00:46,340
- Oh, you wait and see.

1323
01:00:46,340 --> 01:00:48,983
This makes beautiful pictures.

1324
01:00:52,938 --> 01:00:53,880
- You want buildings, listen,

1325
01:00:53,880 --> 01:00:55,520
this cities lousy with building.

1326
01:00:55,520 --> 01:00:56,590
Come with me.

1327
01:00:58,630 --> 01:01:00,278
- Watch out!

1328
01:01:00,278 --> 01:01:02,718
- Oh, I'm so, excuse me.

1329
01:01:02,718 --> 01:01:03,551
Oh, god.

1330
01:01:04,530 --> 01:01:05,718
Sorry.

1331
01:01:05,718 --> 01:01:07,280
(laughing)

1332
01:01:07,280 --> 01:01:08,640
How was your weekend?

1333
01:01:08,640 --> 01:01:11,380
- My weekend was productive.

1334
01:01:11,380 --> 01:01:13,312
I came in Saturday went
through the messages.

1335
01:01:13,312 --> 01:01:15,600
(alert buzzing)
- Ma'am, try again, please.

1336
01:01:16,673 --> 01:01:18,493
Have you got any keys.
- I know why you're happy.

1337
01:01:19,426 --> 01:01:20,826
- I swore I wouldn't let on.

1338
01:01:21,770 --> 01:01:22,650
You can tell.

1339
01:01:22,650 --> 01:01:23,940
- I was talking about the Yankee's

1340
01:01:23,940 --> 01:01:26,030
taking two out of three in Boston.

1341
01:01:26,030 --> 01:01:27,984
What are you talking about?

1342
01:01:27,984 --> 01:01:28,817
- You won't like it.

1343
01:01:28,817 --> 01:01:31,033
You're wrong, but you'll disapprove.

1344
01:01:32,020 --> 01:01:34,170
- A guy, a drinker?

1345
01:01:34,170 --> 01:01:35,220
- Doesn't seem to be.

1346
01:01:38,230 --> 01:01:39,063
- Married?

1347
01:01:42,030 --> 01:01:44,550
- Ladies and gentlemen, of the jury,

1348
01:01:44,550 --> 01:01:46,363
this is a capital case.

1349
01:01:48,070 --> 01:01:49,070
- How married is he?

1350
01:01:51,550 --> 01:01:54,443
- We will show you the
scene of the murder.

1351
01:01:55,800 --> 01:01:58,160
You will see how the accused

1352
01:01:58,160 --> 01:02:00,270
waited in a car borrowed from a friend

1353
01:02:01,540 --> 01:02:04,130
and how he followed Lester
Purchase from his delivery

1354
01:02:04,130 --> 01:02:06,390
at the Chadwell Market on the 1200-block

1355
01:02:06,390 --> 01:02:07,650
of Queens Parkway South

1356
01:02:08,610 --> 01:02:12,290
to the Zhukov Brothers
Market on the 1800-block.

1357
01:02:12,290 --> 01:02:15,370
You will hear scientific testimony

1358
01:02:15,370 --> 01:02:17,570
of a fatal shot to the head,

1359
01:02:17,570 --> 01:02:22,433
which the accused
delivered to Mr. Purchase.

1360
01:02:25,350 --> 01:02:30,270
And after he had stolen $513 in cash,

1361
01:02:33,610 --> 01:02:35,340
and after he had taken the life

1362
01:02:37,280 --> 01:02:39,533
of this hard-working man, this good man,

1363
01:02:40,960 --> 01:02:44,770
Raymond Bolzer took a
single gold wedding ring

1364
01:02:45,610 --> 01:02:48,513
from the third finger of
the victim's left hand.

1365
01:02:50,800 --> 01:02:52,200
Now, ladies and gentlemen,

1366
01:02:52,200 --> 01:02:55,563
that ring was missing for a long time.

1367
01:02:56,500 --> 01:03:00,130
But it was found in the home

1368
01:03:00,130 --> 01:03:01,933
of the aunt of the accused,

1369
01:03:04,350 --> 01:03:06,840
a woman who says she's
never seen that ring before,

1370
01:03:06,840 --> 01:03:09,640
a woman who never knew Lester Purchase.

1371
01:03:09,640 --> 01:03:13,060
There is only one link

1372
01:03:13,060 --> 01:03:15,050
between Lester Purchase

1373
01:03:15,050 --> 01:03:17,263
and the aunt of Raymond Bolzer.

1374
01:03:18,870 --> 01:03:23,793
And, ladies and gentlemen,
that is Raymond Bolzer.

1375
01:03:32,743 --> 01:03:33,758
(telephones ringing in offices)

1376
01:03:33,758 --> 01:03:36,040
(people chattering)

1377
01:03:36,040 --> 01:03:37,540
- [Mary Beth] I've got it.

1378
01:03:37,540 --> 01:03:39,200
Thank you, ma'am.

1379
01:03:39,200 --> 01:03:40,140
You're being used.

1380
01:03:40,140 --> 01:03:41,100
- You better believe it.

1381
01:03:41,100 --> 01:03:43,540
Used and useful, yes.

1382
01:03:43,540 --> 01:03:45,440
- This is not some knee jerk moral thing.

1383
01:03:45,440 --> 01:03:47,270
I'm thinking about what he's doing to you.

1384
01:03:47,270 --> 01:03:48,410
Hello.

1385
01:03:48,410 --> 01:03:50,090
Mister, uh?

1386
01:03:50,090 --> 01:03:50,923
Oaks.

1387
01:03:50,923 --> 01:03:51,850
Mr. Oaks, please.

1388
01:03:51,850 --> 01:03:52,800
- Am I happy?

1389
01:03:52,800 --> 01:03:54,500
Let me be happy.

1390
01:03:54,500 --> 01:03:55,333
- It's Investigator Lacey

1391
01:03:55,333 --> 01:03:57,570
with the District Attorney's office.

1392
01:03:57,570 --> 01:03:58,699
Thank you.

1393
01:03:58,699 --> 01:03:59,610
You come to me when it's over.

1394
01:03:59,610 --> 01:04:00,980
Tell me how happy you are.

1395
01:04:00,980 --> 01:04:02,390
- Cagney.

1396
01:04:02,390 --> 01:04:03,640
Yeah, Lee, hi, what's up?

1397
01:04:06,250 --> 01:04:07,083
Sure.

1398
01:04:08,450 --> 01:04:09,620
Sure, yeah.

1399
01:04:09,620 --> 01:04:10,453
Right away.

1400
01:04:10,453 --> 01:04:11,286
Okay, thanks.

1401
01:04:12,690 --> 01:04:13,523
- What's up?

1402
01:04:13,523 --> 01:04:15,310
- They're holding a guy
who could be my shooter.

1403
01:04:15,310 --> 01:04:16,730
I'm gonna go take a look at him.

1404
01:04:16,730 --> 01:04:17,790
- Great.
- Would that be

1405
01:04:17,790 --> 01:04:19,040
a kick in the head?

1406
01:04:19,040 --> 01:04:20,010
Beep me if you need me.

1407
01:04:20,010 --> 01:04:20,843
- Go.

1408
01:04:22,450 --> 01:04:24,763
Mr. Oaks, it's Investigator.

1409
01:04:26,750 --> 01:04:28,103
Nice to meet you too, sir.

1410
01:04:30,720 --> 01:04:32,870
You called last week
about the Bolzer case.

1411
01:04:35,090 --> 01:04:36,280
Sure.

1412
01:04:36,280 --> 01:04:37,270
No, no, sure.

1413
01:04:37,270 --> 01:04:38,123
It matters.

1414
01:04:39,520 --> 01:04:40,593
Where is your store?

1415
01:04:43,791 --> 01:04:44,880
(people chattering)

1416
01:04:44,880 --> 01:04:47,137
- I'll take a look.
- is this fresh?

1417
01:04:51,940 --> 01:04:52,773
- Mr. Oaks.

1418
01:04:54,420 --> 01:04:56,670
- Oh, you're with the DA?

1419
01:04:56,670 --> 01:04:58,133
- [Mary Beth] Investigator Lacey.

1420
01:04:59,690 --> 01:05:01,700
- I've been getting
called by someone working

1421
01:05:01,700 --> 01:05:04,840
for Bolzer's lawyer every day.

1422
01:05:04,840 --> 01:05:05,740
They don't let up.

1423
01:05:07,850 --> 01:05:08,683
I've been putting them off

1424
01:05:08,683 --> 01:05:10,420
because I wanted to
talk to you guys first.

1425
01:05:10,420 --> 01:05:12,530
I don't wanna say or do
nothing to screw things up.

1426
01:05:12,530 --> 01:05:13,830
- We appreciate that, sir.

1427
01:05:15,208 --> 01:05:16,280
What was it you wanted us to know?

1428
01:05:16,280 --> 01:05:17,380
- Well, it's a little thing.

1429
01:05:17,380 --> 01:05:19,060
But I'm sure you guys got it wrong.

1430
01:05:19,060 --> 01:05:20,540
- [Mary Beth] What?

1431
01:05:20,540 --> 01:05:22,060
- I played card with Lester Purchase.

1432
01:05:22,060 --> 01:05:24,310
I know him maybe, I don't know, 15 years.

1433
01:05:24,310 --> 01:05:26,530
I see him deliver in here twice a week,

1434
01:05:26,530 --> 01:05:29,060
and on Tuesday nights we played cards.

1435
01:05:29,060 --> 01:05:30,110
He never wore a ring.

1436
01:05:31,140 --> 01:05:33,840
- You can't remember Mr.
Purchase wearing a ring?

1437
01:05:33,840 --> 01:05:35,980
- Listen, you can believe
me or not believe me.

1438
01:05:35,980 --> 01:05:37,240
Don't play with my words.

1439
01:05:37,240 --> 01:05:39,363
I never saw Lester Purchase with a ring.

1440
01:05:41,340 --> 01:05:42,173
- Yes, sir.

1441
01:05:43,794 --> 01:05:44,627
Those are nice.

1442
01:05:44,627 --> 01:05:45,460
- They sure are.

1443
01:05:45,460 --> 01:05:46,880
- What'd get for those?

1444
01:05:46,880 --> 01:05:48,170
- Special today.

1445
01:05:48,170 --> 01:05:49,922
The DA Special we call it.

1446
01:05:49,922 --> 01:05:52,005
(laughs)

1447
01:05:59,910 --> 01:06:01,210
- [Christine] Number five.

1448
01:06:02,660 --> 01:06:03,888
- You wanna take another second?

1449
01:06:03,888 --> 01:06:06,180
- [Christine] It's number five, Lee.

1450
01:06:06,180 --> 01:06:07,080
- Thank you, ma'am.

1451
01:06:07,080 --> 01:06:08,173
- [Christine] You're welcome.

1452
01:06:08,173 --> 01:06:09,873
- That okay with you, Miss O'Neil?

1453
01:06:12,650 --> 01:06:14,550
- Yes.
- Keep number five in the pen.

1454
01:06:16,500 --> 01:06:18,250
- You get all the easy cases, don't you?

1455
01:06:18,250 --> 01:06:19,083
- Oh, no.

1456
01:06:19,083 --> 01:06:21,170
This will get gummed up.

1457
01:06:21,170 --> 01:06:24,017
Now we have to find out who hired him.

1458
01:06:24,017 --> 01:06:24,850
- "Who hired him?"

1459
01:06:24,850 --> 01:06:26,630
Your obsessed Costa Rican boyfriend.

1460
01:06:26,630 --> 01:06:28,690
- I called him in, you know.

1461
01:06:28,690 --> 01:06:30,400
He claims that when he
heard about the shooting,

1462
01:06:30,400 --> 01:06:32,850
his first thought was,
"It should've been me."

1463
01:06:32,850 --> 01:06:34,110
- What?
- He says

1464
01:06:34,110 --> 01:06:37,490
that the shooter mistook
Gabriel Ramos for himself.

1465
01:06:37,490 --> 01:06:40,020
That he had been threatened
to keep away from Darcy Wylie

1466
01:06:40,020 --> 01:06:41,433
or else he'd end up dead.

1467
01:06:42,300 --> 01:06:43,690
Nuts.

1468
01:06:43,690 --> 01:06:45,082
- [Christine] He didn't happen
to say who threatened him.

1469
01:06:45,082 --> 01:06:47,260
- (scoffs) No, he didn't have a name.

1470
01:06:47,260 --> 01:06:48,770
Of course, he didn't.

1471
01:06:48,770 --> 01:06:53,770
But he offered a detailed
description of a giant guy,

1472
01:06:53,920 --> 01:06:57,030
fat big, not muscle big,

1473
01:06:57,030 --> 01:07:00,266
who claimed to be a private investigator.

1474
01:07:00,266 --> 01:07:03,235
(dramatic music)

1475
01:07:03,235 --> 01:07:04,635
- And he didn't have a name.

1476
01:07:04,635 --> 01:07:06,560
- No, I said he didn't have a name.

1477
01:07:06,560 --> 01:07:08,380
Just a description.

1478
01:07:08,380 --> 01:07:10,900
He claims that he saw
this guy following Darcy

1479
01:07:10,900 --> 01:07:12,330
a few months ago.

1480
01:07:12,330 --> 01:07:15,260
Now I'm supposed to
locate this un-named PI,

1481
01:07:15,260 --> 01:07:17,030
and find out who hired him

1482
01:07:17,030 --> 01:07:18,513
to threaten my prime suspect.

1483
01:07:19,739 --> 01:07:22,670
(papers rustling)

1484
01:07:22,670 --> 01:07:24,562
I don't believe any of it.

1485
01:07:24,562 --> 01:07:27,312
(dramatic music)

1486
01:07:28,430 --> 01:07:30,007
But like you said, "This is an easy one.

1487
01:07:30,007 --> 01:07:32,220
"I should relax and enjoy it."

1488
01:07:32,220 --> 01:07:33,870
Still, you never know.

1489
01:07:35,451 --> 01:07:38,534
(gentle piano music)

1490
01:08:29,876 --> 01:08:32,459
(gentle music)

1491
01:08:33,381 --> 01:08:34,381
- Rough day.

1492
01:08:36,523 --> 01:08:39,380
- The ghosts are already dancing.

1493
01:08:39,380 --> 01:08:41,547
(sighing)

1494
01:08:51,892 --> 01:08:54,380
- Now the important thing is
keep breathing that's all.

1495
01:08:54,380 --> 01:08:55,314
Okay?

1496
01:08:55,314 --> 01:08:56,910
(people chattering)

1497
01:08:56,910 --> 01:08:57,743
You all right?

1498
01:09:00,590 --> 01:09:01,540
You look good, Ron?

1499
01:09:02,593 --> 01:09:04,460
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

1500
01:09:04,460 --> 01:09:05,400
Now you just,

1501
01:09:05,400 --> 01:09:07,550
you wait here a sec
while I go see if I can

1502
01:09:08,400 --> 01:09:10,720
tell how soon before you're called.

1503
01:09:10,720 --> 01:09:12,133
All right, tuck your shirt in.

1504
01:09:13,260 --> 01:09:14,093
Sit down.

1505
01:09:18,264 --> 01:09:19,700
(paper rustling)

1506
01:09:19,700 --> 01:09:21,510
- I'm opening an envelop.

1507
01:09:21,510 --> 01:09:22,853
I'm removing a ring.

1508
01:09:24,830 --> 01:09:26,313
I'm holding a gold ring,

1509
01:09:27,310 --> 01:09:29,530
fairly large sized,

1510
01:09:29,530 --> 01:09:31,253
with faceted edges,

1511
01:09:32,190 --> 01:09:34,320
and an inscription inside.

1512
01:09:34,320 --> 01:09:35,870
- Can you read the inscription?

1513
01:09:39,047 --> 01:09:42,000
- It says, "12/28/59."

1514
01:09:42,000 --> 01:09:45,503
- Is this the ring found
at the home of Grace Pound?

1515
01:09:45,503 --> 01:09:46,800
- Yes, it is.

1516
01:09:46,800 --> 01:09:50,803
- Your Honor, entered into
evidence is State's 59.

1517
01:09:52,690 --> 01:09:53,740
No further questions.

1518
01:09:54,823 --> 01:09:57,573
(dramatic music)

1519
01:10:04,260 --> 01:10:05,280
- [Mary Beth] You walked
out of here yesterday

1520
01:10:05,280 --> 01:10:06,930
with the key to the file cabinet.

1521
01:10:08,420 --> 01:10:09,930
- Yes, I did.

1522
01:10:09,930 --> 01:10:10,763
Sorry.

1523
01:10:12,610 --> 01:10:14,023
- [Mary Beth] Give it to me please.

1524
01:10:14,890 --> 01:10:16,840
- Here, hello to you too.

1525
01:10:16,840 --> 01:10:17,673
- Thanks.

1526
01:10:21,030 --> 01:10:22,550
Christine.

1527
01:10:22,550 --> 01:10:23,383
- What?

1528
01:10:25,460 --> 01:10:30,000
- Christine, I believe that
the wedding ring I found

1529
01:10:30,000 --> 01:10:31,330
is planted evidence.

1530
01:10:31,330 --> 01:10:32,630
- What?

1531
01:10:32,630 --> 01:10:34,580
- I spoke with a very credible witness.

1532
01:10:35,430 --> 01:10:37,740
Lester Purchase didn't wear a ring.

1533
01:10:37,740 --> 01:10:40,460
- The ring is in evidence.

1534
01:10:40,460 --> 01:10:43,330
- The autopsy mentions arthritis.

1535
01:10:43,330 --> 01:10:44,163
Now look at his hand.

1536
01:10:44,163 --> 01:10:44,996
See his hand.

1537
01:10:46,180 --> 01:10:48,130
Well, his joints are swollen.

1538
01:10:48,130 --> 01:10:51,270
But a lot of people with
swollen joints wear rings.

1539
01:10:51,270 --> 01:10:53,403
- How'd Bolzer get the ring off?

1540
01:10:53,403 --> 01:10:55,350
- Well, I don't know.

1541
01:10:55,350 --> 01:10:57,770
- Remember the interview
with Mrs. Purchase?

1542
01:10:57,770 --> 01:10:58,970
- Yeah.
- I wanna play you

1543
01:10:58,970 --> 01:10:59,803
a piece of it.

1544
01:11:00,830 --> 01:11:01,663
Excuse me.

1545
01:11:02,510 --> 01:11:03,773
- Geez, Mary Beth.

1546
01:11:07,180 --> 01:11:08,013
- Listen to her.

1547
01:11:09,203 --> 01:11:13,830
- [Mrs. Purchase] On the
inside it says "12/28/59."

1548
01:11:13,830 --> 01:11:14,680
That's our wedding day.

1549
01:11:14,680 --> 01:11:17,500
- [Mike] You have the
ring in your possession?

1550
01:11:17,500 --> 01:11:18,600
- [Mrs. Purchase] No, sir.

1551
01:11:18,600 --> 01:11:20,010
- [Mike] Was your
husband wearing that ring

1552
01:11:20,010 --> 01:11:21,780
the last time you saw him?

1553
01:11:21,780 --> 01:11:22,613
- Here.

1554
01:11:24,016 --> 01:11:25,943
- [Mrs. Purchase] Dear
God, make me strong.

1555
01:11:28,378 --> 01:11:29,923
(coughs) Yes, sir.

1556
01:11:31,040 --> 01:11:33,540
(tape clicks)

1557
01:11:34,770 --> 01:11:36,250
- Her little prayer.

1558
01:11:36,250 --> 01:11:37,597
- She's just dreading the news,

1559
01:11:37,597 --> 01:11:39,437
"They're gonna tell me
they found his ring.

1560
01:11:39,437 --> 01:11:41,310
"Dear God, make me strong."

1561
01:11:41,310 --> 01:11:46,310
- Or, "Here comes the lie I have to tell.

1562
01:11:46,547 --> 01:11:48,824
"Dear God, make me strong."

1563
01:11:48,824 --> 01:11:51,934
(tape rewinding)

1564
01:11:51,934 --> 01:11:56,311
- [Mrs. Purchase] Dear
God, make me strong.

1565
01:11:56,311 --> 01:11:57,883
(coughs) Yes, sir.

1566
01:12:00,751 --> 01:12:02,551
- Mary Beth, you found the evidence.

1567
01:12:05,960 --> 01:12:07,293
- Mike Foy led me to it.

1568
01:12:08,760 --> 01:12:10,550
I think, he planned the whole thing.

1569
01:12:10,550 --> 01:12:11,383
- Hold it.

1570
01:12:13,210 --> 01:12:14,043
Hold it.

1571
01:12:18,490 --> 01:12:20,200
Did he enter the room before you?

1572
01:12:20,200 --> 01:12:21,450
- I went first.

1573
01:12:21,450 --> 01:12:23,050
- Was there ever a time when he was alone

1574
01:12:23,050 --> 01:12:24,440
with the shoeboxes?

1575
01:12:24,440 --> 01:12:26,500
- I was there the whole time.

1576
01:12:26,500 --> 01:12:29,440
- [Christine] Did you see him
drop anything into the box?

1577
01:12:29,440 --> 01:12:30,273
- No.

1578
01:12:30,273 --> 01:12:32,460
- Well, then cut it out!

1579
01:12:32,460 --> 01:12:34,323
- Where's the key to the file cabinet?

1580
01:12:35,210 --> 01:12:37,630
- I gave it to you two seconds ago.

1581
01:12:37,630 --> 01:12:39,050
- I don't have it.

1582
01:12:39,050 --> 01:12:39,950
Check your drawer.

1583
01:12:40,860 --> 01:12:42,620
- It's not in my drawer.

1584
01:12:42,620 --> 01:12:44,523
Don't you remember I gave it to you.

1585
01:12:47,910 --> 01:12:49,310
How'd that get in my drawer?

1586
01:12:50,540 --> 01:12:53,323
- Was there ever a time that
I was alone with that drawer?

1587
01:12:59,221 --> 01:13:01,721
(key jangles)

1588
01:13:04,206 --> 01:13:06,206
(sighs)

1589
01:13:08,570 --> 01:13:10,660
- The jury's already seen the ring.

1590
01:13:10,660 --> 01:13:11,593
It's out there.

1591
01:13:14,800 --> 01:13:15,633
Are you certain?

1592
01:13:16,930 --> 01:13:19,080
- It's a moral certainty, sir.

1593
01:13:19,080 --> 01:13:21,130
I can't tell you I saw anything I didn't.

1594
01:13:22,622 --> 01:13:23,455
(sighs)

1595
01:13:23,455 --> 01:13:25,260
- Does Foy know what you know?

1596
01:13:25,260 --> 01:13:27,380
- We haven't said anything.

1597
01:13:27,380 --> 01:13:29,890
- We thought in the event
that he was charged, sir.

1598
01:13:29,890 --> 01:13:31,450
- Hey, I don't wanna hear about it.

1599
01:13:31,450 --> 01:13:32,520
You're talking about charging

